[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "YouTube says it\u2019s not slowing down Firefox \u2014 just ad blockers", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"YouTube logo on an abstract background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/11gfsTwQQBZzC01kk6ive6lVMSQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72890223/acastro_STK092_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZsjIXO\">Users on <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/firefox/comments/17zdpkl/this_behaviour_from_google_is_beyond_disgusting/?context=3\">Reddit</a> and <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=38345968\">Hacker News</a> are complaining that YouTube seems to have inserted an intentional five-second delay before video pages will load in Mozilla\u2019s Firefox and occasionally some other browsers. YouTube tells <em>The Verge</em> that these users are right about the delay, but the browser has nothing to do with it \u2014 it\u2019s part of the company\u2019s efforts to quash ad blockers across all platforms.</p>\n<p id=\"jpj0U8\">\u201cIn the past week, users using ad blockers may have exp", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970721/google-youtube-ad-blocker-five-second-delay-firefox-chrome", "date_published": "2023-11-21T23:23:51+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "OpenAI drops a big new ChatGPT feature with a joke about its CEO drama", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A rendition of OpenAI\u2019s logo, which looks like a stylized whirlpool.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/X58X72btnP9Hf-bWds4ylJdFOk8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72890076/STK149_AI_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Otimzy\">ChatGPT\u2019s voice feature is now available to all users for free. In <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OpenAI/status/1727065166188274145\">a post on X (formerly Twitter)</a>, OpenAI announced users can now tap the headphones icon to use their voice to talk with ChatGPT in the mobile app, as well as get an audible response.</p>\n<p id=\"z7Ef00\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/25/23886699/chatgpt-pictures-voice-commands-ai-chatbot-openai\">OpenAI first rolled out the ability</a> to prompt ChatGPT with your voice and images in September, but it only made the feature available to paying users.</p>\n<p id=\"vIYRoS\">The release comes as OpenAI\u2019s staff ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971489/openai-chatgpt-voice-feature-ceo-drama", "date_published": "2023-11-21T22:14:18+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Best gaming laptop in 2023: seven laptops to get your game on", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6dUmb-5YpYUIMGi1Z90F0o9c7RI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/68856650/236647_Best_Gaming_Laptop_buying_guide_WJoel.15.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From midsized and midrange stars to big, beefy monsters, these are the best technically portable gaming rigs you can get. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22295181/best-gaming-laptop\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22295181/best-gaming-laptop", "date_published": "2023-11-21T21:35:59+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Flipboard is abandoning X for Mastodon", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Zz1gjtvPicE2APQsIly7_bw2v80=/110x0:1202x728/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889891/Screen_Shot_2023_11_21_at_12.22.26_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Flipboard</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UIOLCw\">Flipboard is the latest company to end its presence on X, the platform formerly known as Twitter. In a Medium <a href=\"https://flipboard.medium.com/flipboard-steps-back-from-tweeting-b0f4af1f4ffc\">post</a> published Tuesday, the company said it would no longer be \u201cactively monitoring or posting updates on X,\u201d save for the occasional retweet. Instead, Flipboard will be refocusing its efforts on Mastodon and other open social platforms.</p>\n<p id=\"2wbJ1V\">The reasons for Flipboard\u2019s departure from X appear to be two-fold: X\u2019s more lax moderation policies under Elon Musk\u2019s leadership, which has led to a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/14/23960430/x-twitter-ccdh-hate-speech-moderation-israel", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971398/flipboard-x-twitter-mastodon-quitting", "date_published": "2023-11-21T21:22:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "GameMaker ditches subscription model for indie developers", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Hotline Miami 2\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/U7pojRrXM3M5xnZfLKkEcCMdCE4=/110x0:991x587/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889867/HLM2_Screen_5.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Devolver Digital</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GW8EbY\">Christmas has come early for indie / solo game developers. GameMaker, the game engine software program used to make <em>Undertale</em>, <em>Chicory: A Colorful Tale</em>, <em>Hotline Miami 2</em>, and more, has <a href=\"https://gamemaker.io/en/blog/gamemaker-free-platforms\">announced that it\u2019s making significant changes to its pricing structure</a> \u2014 but don\u2019t worry, they\u2019re the good kind of changes.</p>\n<p id=\"dPlPLb\">Starting today, GameMaker will be free to use for noncommercial, non-console projects, and the company is eliminating its indie / creator tier monthly subscription fee in favor of a one-time paid licensing fee of $99. Additionally, if you\u2019re currently enrolled at", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971394/gamemaker-free-indie-creator-licensing-fee-unity", "date_published": "2023-11-21T21:16:14+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Dave Filoni gets the keys to the Star Wars franchise", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Dave Filoni in front of a Star Wars Celebration backdrop. He\u2019s wearing a cowboy hat, yeehaw.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gtDJ6JMbWKwqUdgT1W_n5XhZnW8=/0x107:7470x5087/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889838/1480779538.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Dave Filoni in April at Star Wars Celebration 2023 in London.</em> | Photo by Jeff Spicer / Getty Images for Disney</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"dUFJY4\">Dave Filoni just got rewarded for the success of <em>Ahsoka, The Mandalorian, </em>and other <em>Star Wars </em>shows with a promotion to chief creative officer of Lucasfilm. According to details in a new <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2023/11/star-wars-ahsoka-dave-filoni\"><em>Vanity Fair</em> interview</a>, he\u2019ll work alongside head developer Carrie Beck, reporting directly to Kathleen Kennedy, and together, the duo will determine the direction of <em>Star Wars</em> overall \u2014 not just the streaming shows.</p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971309/dave-filoni-star-wars-chief-creative-officer-lucasfilm-asoka", "date_published": "2023-11-21T21:08:42+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Tesla\u00a0workers report explosions, concussions, and grisly robot injuries at Texas factory", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Elon\u2019s Expanding Empire In Texas\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2uImeqfYaFPDrFNJ3W2OGjv0SRs=/0x165:3971x2812/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889778/1236440290.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PeEXGJ\">As Tesla prepares to deliver its first Cybertrucks to customers, a new report paints a grisly picture of the Texas factory where the truck is being built, including a casting machine explosion and a robot allegedly goring a worker. </p>\n<p id=\"sDe8Kb\"><em>The Information</em> <a href=\"https://www.theinformation.com/articles/at-teslas-giant-texas-factory-injuries-and-safety-lapses-mount\">reported some of the gruesome incidents</a> that have occurred at the Gigafactory in Austin, Texas, where one out of every 21 workers were reportedly hurt in 2022. The data is derived from the required injury reports Tesla submits to OSHA. </p>\n<p id=\"2VlfYE\">One incident in 2021 involved an engineer who a", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971138/tesla-gigafactory-austin-texas-injury-reports-robot-claw-explosion", "date_published": "2023-11-21T20:48:24+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best magnetic chargers for your MagSafe iPhone", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of repeating magnetic charging pucks and magnetic power banks, tiled across a dark blue background with a subtle lightning bolt pattern.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g2aclZB2pruyr8nK4GDEe6sVtI8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/71769681/226442_magnetic_wireless_charger_buying_guide_K_Radtke.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Making sense of Apple\u2019s messy MagSafe charging ecosystem, where the first-party options are far from the best.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone", "date_published": "2023-11-21T20:25:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "OpenAI rival Anthropic makes its Claude chatbot even more useful", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Anthropic\u2019s logo \u2014 the outline of a head surrounded by three more larger outlines of heads, and a star-shaped set of lines emerging from a center point of the smallest head and bursting out in seven different lengths of line, terminating in filled-in circles. The background is orange.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xuNqK0XIDJpxWDSwJi1sSWSh-_Y=/225x0:2655x1620/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889672/Claude_2.1_Blog.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Anthropic gives Claude more abilities.</em> | Image: Anthropic</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"nU3exR\">While OpenAI is in the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23966325/openai-sam-altman-fired-turmoil-chatgpt\">middle of an existential crisis</a>, there\u2019s a new chatbot update from Anthropic, the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/3/23584540/google-anthropic-investment-300-million-openai-chatgpt-rival-claude\">Google-backed AI startup</a> founded by former OpenAI engineers who lef", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971070/anthropic-claude-2-1-openai-ai-chatbot-update-beta-tools", "date_published": "2023-11-21T20:09:14+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best Xbox controller to buy right now", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A collection of Xbox controllers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rjGvL-Gn6qO3qPgTLmNdccxOND0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70908912/acastro_220505_5198_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From basic and affordable to premium and ultra-customizable, these are the best controllers for Xbox. And they work with PCs, too.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23025443/best-xbox-controllers-one-series-x-s\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23025443/best-xbox-controllers-one-series-x-s", "date_published": "2023-11-21T20:04:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sonos plans a 2024 loaded with new products  \u2014 including headphones and a set-top box", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sonos Era 100 speaker in a kitchen setting beside an iPad and toaster.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bA1U80Q6UZ1ox1eN-ucHRIDEZig=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889648/DSCF0435.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5xghyy\">As the company has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/15/23962936/sonos-major-new-product-coming-2024-tease\">strongly hinted in recent weeks</a>, Sonos will indeed release its first-ever pair of headphones next year. That\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-21/sonos-plans-400-500-headphones-tv-set-top-box-video-roam-2-new-sound-bar#xj4y7vzkg\">according to <em>Bloomberg</em>\u2019s Mark Gurman</a>, who pegs a release as early as April. The over-ear headphones are rumored to cost between $400 and $500 \u2014 very premium territory for a company that\u2019s brand new to the category. </p>\n<p id=\"ljmI0E\">At least one marquee feature will be their ability to synchronize music", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971209/sonos-headphones-set-top-box-arc-2-leak", "date_published": "2023-11-21T20:00:56+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Raise your hand to speak, please", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A woman on a video call raising her hand.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oTqqGScBpPcbvZnp8_uBn4PboBk=/151x0:1681x1020/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889542/Screenshot_2023_11_21_at_1.55.29_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Video conference service Google Meet is adding gesture recognition to make it easier to ask a question during a video call.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3hEkTK\">Google Meet can now recognize when your physical hand is raised on camera during group video calls and alert the host. This means you don\u2019t have to fiddle with clicking the \u201chand raise\u201d button on the screen and accidentally send a clapping emoji to everyone in the call (I speak from experience). </p>\n<p id=\"Vnw5Zo\">In a blog post published today, <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2023/11/google-meet-hand-raise-gesture-detection.html\">Google announced the feature is now rolling out to Google Workspace busine", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971246/google-meet-gesture-recognition-hand-raise-new-feature", "date_published": "2023-11-21T19:37:48+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best phone to buy right now", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of various phones from Apple, Google, and Samsung.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5XZQBkz4EU3BpoTxpPWA5e_T3-Y=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/68490961/226301_Best_Phone_Lede_Update_WJoel_001.17.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by William Joel / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Bad news: flagship phones cost a small fortune these days. Good news: we can help you pick the right one and get the most for your money.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22163811/best-phone\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22163811/best-phone", "date_published": "2023-11-21T19:12:18+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Binance criminal settlement could include a $4 billion fine and CEO\u2019s guilty plea", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Binance logo on a blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sgfyeHd4n1lOXCHfT18-c1hRwJM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72889134/STK018_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_11_BINANCE.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"x6reKA\">Binance owner and CEO Changpeng \u201cCZ\u201d Zhao has agreed to step down and plead guilty to breaking anti-money laundering laws, according to <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/finance/currencies/binance-ceo-changpeng-zhao-step-down-plead-guilty-01f72a40\">reports from <em>The Wall Street Journal</em></a> and <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidjeans/2023/11/21/binance-ceo-cz-in-discussions-to-step-down-as-criminal-investigation-ends/?sh=1c9357af4aca\"><em>Forbes</em></a>. This comes as part of the major settlement the Department of Justice is expected to announce this afternoon, which will reportedly require Binance to fork over $4.3 bil", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23971066/binance-ceo-changpeng-zhao-step-down", "date_published": "2023-11-21T18:15:07+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "A24\u2019s Dream Scenario is a shapeshifting parable about our obsessions with viral fame", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A balding middle-aged man wearing glasses, a blue suit, and an armored glove on one hand as he leans over to rest his arm on the back of a leather chair.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GalCLLvxRg3DdrJTrM32wdljels=/0x38:4451x3005/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888630/https___cdn.sanity.io_images_xq1bjtf4_production_e8d51dadc7b01374e498728d272484a95f5ef86a_6000x4000.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Nicolas Cage as Paul Matthews.</em> | Image: A24</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Writer / director Kristoffer Borgli\u2019s Dream Scenario capitalizes on Nicolas Cage\u2019s status as a living legend to tell a brilliant story about the perils of fame.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23965979/dream-scenario-review-a24-nicolas-cage\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23965979/dream-scenario-review-a24-nicolas-cage", "date_published": "2023-11-21T16:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Bad business is breaking the smart home \u2014 good regulation can fix it", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a living room full of smart devices that are connected by strings to a marionette handle. The vague language of a contract floats ominously above everything.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/L0_YOij4rZ7bGxpIpabv4ULu-k8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888587/236928_Smart_Home_Contracts_7_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Business arrangements and opaque contracts have broken the pitch of the smart home. Better regulation can fix this problem.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23970749/smart-home-broken-policy-fixes\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23970749/smart-home-broken-policy-fixes", "date_published": "2023-11-21T16:15:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "8BitDo\u2019s NES-style keyboard has returned to its lowest price yet", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"8BitDo Retro Keyboard on a desk next to NES-themed buttons, controller, and SNES cartridges.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PS7p-bPhTLceIcDQ1RfxGWgYLiw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888568/236859_8BitDo_keyboard_BOTM_JPorter_0008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>8BitDo\u2019s Retro Mechanical Keyboard is a unique gift under $100 that\u2019s perfect for Nintendo fans.</em> | Photo by Jon Porter / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fG1bu2\">Let\u2019s be honest: most keyboards are boring necessities that you\u2019re not likely to find at the top of anybody\u2019s Christmas wishlist. But every now and then, a keyboard comes along that\u2019s so cool, anyone could get excited about it. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23934698/8bitdo-nes-keyboard-experiment-button-of-the-month\"><strong>8BitDo\u2019s Retro Mechanical Keyboard</strong></a> is one of those unicorns, and right now, it\u2019s down to an all-time low of $89.99 ($10 off) at <a href=\"h", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970028/8bitdo-retro-mechanical-keyboard-deal-sale", "date_published": "2023-11-21T16:08:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Apple\u2019s AirTag drops to a rare low price", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A close-up image depicting a set of hands holding a selection of Apple AirTags.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/G7QxDwp_einMjErNV7-QewndDnU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888432/vpavic_4547_20210421_0131.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Our favorite Bluetooth tracker for iPhone owners is available starting at just $23.99 for a single AirTag.</em> | Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NEIWXR\">It\u2019s the time of year again when utter chaos descends upon airports nationwide. That means the chances of losing your luggage are higher than usual, so it\u2019s worth preparing for the commotion if you\u2019re planning to travel.</p>\n<p id=\"TS6yp3\">Right now, you can buy a single <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/22/22396693/apple-airtag-location-tracker-hands-on-find-my-privacy-safety\"><strong>AirTag</strong></a> for just $23.99 ($5 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Apple-MX532AM-A-AirTag", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23969948/apple-airtag-bluetooth-tracker-black-friday-deal-sale", "date_published": "2023-11-21T15:38:12+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "What\u2019s on your desk, Nathan Edwards?", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Desk and bookcase, with window at right.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zsGJAxsrGKhPyxk9BoFV90dIfDk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888350/236931_What_s_on_your_desk_Nathan_Edwards_NEdwards_0014.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Nathan Edwards / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Two desks, three computers, and countless keyboards.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23969229/home-office-setup-desk-chair-laptop-desktop-nathan-edwards\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23969229/home-office-setup-desk-chair-laptop-desktop-nathan-edwards", "date_published": "2023-11-21T15:07:38+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Verge\u2019s 2023 holiday gift guide for kids", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of hands holding various products on a brightly colored background of stars.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BuamjMoqrNyuzYDmwJ1sITdned8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888273/236830_FOR_KIDS_Gift_Guide_Art_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by Amelia Holowaty Krales and Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Let us help you find all kinds of gifts for all kinds of kiddos.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23964428/kids-teens-gifts-unique-ideas-2023-presents-children-tech-gadgets\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23964428/kids-teens-gifts-unique-ideas-2023-presents-children-tech-gadgets", "date_published": "2023-11-21T15:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Fortnite OG will end with a Big Bang", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Promotional art for Fortnite\u2019s Big Bang event.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TPhmGzbctOMR6VK2r2ronwNQ67w=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888240/fortnite_the_big_bang_live_event_1920x1080_8cc212a8f610.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"dSETWz\"><em>Fortnite</em> is currently saturated in nostalgia, thanks to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/6/23948555/fortnite-og-new-season\">the backwards-looking <em>Fortnite</em> OG</a>. But that\u2019s about to change very soon: the battle royale\u2019s next major live event promises \u201ca new beginning\u201d for the game. There aren\u2019t <a href=\"https://www.fortnite.com/news/the-big-bang-event-a-new-beginning-for-fortnite-on-december-2\">many other details</a>, but the event is called The Big Bang, and it kicks off on December 2nd at 2PM ET; as with past events, developer Epic recommends players show up at least 30 minutes early so they don\u2019", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970772/fortnite-big-bang-live-event-date", "date_published": "2023-11-21T14:45:10+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sunbird is shutting down its iMessage app for Android", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person holding an Android phone and using Nothing Chats.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aTNucfke1BsNSxyXRh60gTEZxqE=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888234/Nothing_Chats.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Sunbird powered Nothing Chats, which gave iMessage to Nothing Phone 2, but at a severe privacy cost.</em> | Image: Nothing</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YTRMO1\">Sunbird, the app that brings iMessage to Android, has temporarily shut down the service over \u201csecurity concerns,\u201d <a href=\"https://9to5google.com/2023/11/21/sunbird-shut-down-android-security-concerns/\">as first reported by <em>9to5Google</em></a>. In a notice to users, Sunbird says it has \u201cdecided to pause Sunbird usage for now\u201d while it investigates reports that its messages aren\u2019t actually end-to-end encrypted.</p>\n<p id=\"0kx6dU\">Sunbird launched in 2022 as a messaging app that attempts to put the blue versus green bubble battle to rest. It has on", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970740/sunbird-imessage-app-shut-down-privacy-nothing-chats-phone-2", "date_published": "2023-11-21T14:44:44+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best laptop you can buy in 2023", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0IfaIR7Dkjj3rcSWKLqxQ3XJaEY=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/66770456/236603_Best_Laptops_WJoel.6.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by William Joel / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The best laptops for you, from ultraportables to gaming machines, MacBooks to Chromebooks.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21250695/best-laptops\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/21250695/best-laptops", "date_published": "2023-11-21T13:51:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The World Press Photo Contest\u2019s updated AI rules help define what a modern photograph is", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\u201cHere, The Doors Don\u2019t Know Me\u201d by Mohamed Mahdy, the 2023 winner of the World Press Photo Contest\u2019s Open Format category.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LyTYvTcBGOtghz0iV_1gmEAf9KQ=/0x0:1920x1280/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72888022/WPP_2023Contest_Africa_OPFA_Mohamed_Mahdy.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>\u201cHere, The Doors Don\u2019t Know Me\u201d by Mohamed Mahdy (pictured) was the winning Open Format entry in 2023.</em> | Image: Mohamed Mahdy / Magnum Foundation / World Press Photo Foundation</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7mZMOV\">The World Press Photo Contest has updated its entry rules to exclude submissions for AI-generated imagery, <a href=\"https://www.worldpressphoto.org/news/2023/could-an-ai-image-win-old-version\">just days after announcing</a> that such images could be entered into its Open Format competition category. The World Press Photo Foundation initially said it would <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/CzycrYd", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970682/world-press-photo-contest-generative-ai-rules-guidelines", "date_published": "2023-11-21T13:50:28+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Insta360\u2019s new GoPro-like action cams have flippy screens", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Two GoPro-looking cameras with a flip screen at the top\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/d6eye_0s50ZBusH70RAKQBHyLGU=/0x0:2521x1681/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72887973/Insta360_Ace___Ace_Pro_Key_Visual__No_Copy_.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new Insta360 Ace (right) and Ace Pro (left).</em> | Image: Insta360</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"P3MKyQ\">Insta360\u2019s new action cameras borrow the blocky design of GoPro\u2019s popular Hero series but add the ability to flip up that large 2.4-inch rear touchscreen for easy vlogging. The company\u2019s new \u201cAce\u201d camera starts at $379.99 for the regular model, and there\u2019s a flagship \u201cPro\u201d version for $449.99. The higher-end one is equipped with a Leica Summarit lens and a large 1/1.3-inch image sensor for excellent low-light performance and up to 8K at 24 frames per second recording. Both versions are available now.</p>\n<p id=\"Yt6lkb\">The standard Ace camera model comes with a smaller 1/2", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23969759/insta360-ace-pro-action-camera-gopro", "date_published": "2023-11-21T13:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "This mechanical keyboard has a headphone jack you might actually want to use", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Headphones plugged into keyboard on desk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2bxCZSLxvjxW9_8Et6sThZqMT-s=/0x0:679x453/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72887653/Afeca986656824278a28ed931951fc10d7.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The FiiO KB3 has a built-in DAC and headphone amp.</em> | Image: FiiO</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"oebixu\">The <a href=\"https://www.fiio.com/newsinfo/880928.html\">KB3</a> is a new mechanical keyboard from audio brand FiiO with a built-in headphone jack that stands a good chance of sounding better than the existing 3.5mm output on your desktop computer or laptop. That\u2019s because the headphone jack isn\u2019t just passing through analog audio from your computer, it\u2019s plugged into a combination DAC and headphone amp that\u2019s integrated into the keyboard itself. </p>\n<p id=\"QdhGyj\">So rather than having a headphone cable snaking across your desk to reach your machine, or cluttering up your workspace with a separate D", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970644/fiio-kb3-keyboard-hifi-built-in-headphone-amp-and-dac", "date_published": "2023-11-21T11:49:20+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Braun: Designed to Keep is a book worth holding onto", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo of the cover of the book Braun: Designed to Keep, which features a large black Braun watchface with orange minute hand on white background. The book sits flat on a diagonally striped red, orange and blue table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/s_hfuC-0WKNb1rQkTIFMbrkXQgk=/166x0:2040x1249/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72887432/236903_Braun_design_AKrales_0014.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The cover is adorned with the legendary clockface found on AB1 alarm clock (1987) designed by Dietrich Lubs.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>A century of design \u2014 with and without Dieter Rams \u2014 giving credit where credit is due.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23966605/braun-designed-to-keep-book-review-klaus-kemp\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23966605/braun-designed-to-keep-book-review-klaus-kemp", "date_published": "2023-11-21T09:16:51+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "X sues Media Matters to silence moderation criticism", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of Elon Musk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xa9dTPx51CpPc0UB9sOiY26gIxg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72886874/VRG_Illo_STK022_K_Radtke_Musk_Down_arrow.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Kristen Radtke / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"R62rsm\">X, formerly Twitter, has followed through with owner Elon Musk\u2019s threat to <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/24172816-x-v-media-matters-complaint\">sue the left-leaning nonprofit</a> <em>Media Matters</em>. <a href=\"https://www.mediamatters.org/twitter/musk-endorses-antisemitic-conspiracy-theory-x-has-been-placing-ads-apple-bravo-ibm-oracle\"><em>Media Matters</em> reported last week</a> that X \u201chas been placing ads for major brands\u201d like Apple and IBM \u201cnext to content that touts Adolf Hitler and his Nazi Party.\u201d Musk and X CEO Linda Yaccarino <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/20/23969970/linda-yacca", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/20/23970274/x-elon-musk-media-matters-lawsuit-nazi-ads-filed", "date_published": "2023-11-21T01:58:52+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}]